Class ExperimentManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.nerdherd.ObjectManager.ExperimentManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseListener

    public class ExperimentManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements DatabaseListener
    Singleton ExperimentManager object All Experiment alterations must be done through this control class to maintain consistency Between database and client

                             Region region,
                             boolean locationRequired,
                             boolean publish,
                             ExperimentManager.ExperimentCreateEventListener listener)
        Creates a new experiment in the database with the following
        Parameters:
        title - String - title of experiment
        description - String - description of experiment
        type - int - type of experiment(0=binomial,1=count,2=measurement,3=non-negative)
        minTrials - int - minimum trials required to complete an experiment
        region - Region - Region object with a point location, range, and description
        locationRequired - Boolean - indication whether or not location data must be included with trials
        publish - Boolean - whether or not the experiment is currently published and available for view/participation
        listener - ExperimentCreateEventListener - listener to call back to on successful creation of the experiment.
